[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":737},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F02\u002F18\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F02\u002F18\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F02\u002F18\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F02\u002F18\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it\u002F":713,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F02\u002F18\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it\u002F":722},"\u002Fother\u002F20230218\u002F3618693250\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":696,"date":697,"description":698,"extension":699,"lang":700,"meta":701,"navigation":544,"path":702,"readingMinutes":703,"seo":704,"standalone":705,"stem":706,"tags":707,"tldr":710,"updated":697,"url":711,"__hash__":712},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it.md","What Is Env and When Should You Use It?","8240519673",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":689},"minimark",[11,19,24,32,36,44,47,63,69,75,96,105,118,130,135,161,171,182,193,197,206,215,218,246,257,264,286,292,315,318,321,325,328,331,334,344,350,354,357,364,367,372,378,407,414,423,432,438,619,629,635,642,647,650,653,674,677,686],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"Env","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqjByd5b.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26,27,31],{},"Quick post on what ",[28,29,30],"code",{},".env"," is and when you should use one. If env vars are still fuzzy for you, hopefully this helps clear them up.",[20,33,35],{"id":34},"what-is-env","What is Env",[12,37,38,39,43],{},"Env is short for ",[40,41,42],"strong",{},"Environment"," — environment variables. They're everywhere in both frontend and backend dev.",[12,45,46],{},"What are they for? Usually storing sensitive info — things like:",[48,49,50,54,57,60],"ul",{},[51,52,53],"li",{},"key",[51,55,56],{},"secret",[51,58,59],{},"token",[51,61,62],{},"...etc.",[12,64,65,66,68],{},"We can't hardcode sensitive info in source code, so we stash it in ",[28,67,30],{}," and reference it from code via the env var.",[12,70,71,72,74],{},"Common ",[28,73,30],{}," filenames:",[48,76,77,81,86,91],{},[51,78,79],{},[28,80,30],{},[51,82,83],{},[28,84,85],{},".env.development",[51,87,88],{},[28,89,90],{},".env.production",[51,92,93],{},[28,94,95],{},".env.test",[12,97,98,99,101,102,104],{},"Different files for different environments — use ",[28,100,85],{}," while developing, ",[28,103,90],{}," in production.",[12,106,107,109,110,113,114,117],{},[28,108,30],{}," should ",[40,111,112],{},"never"," be checked into Git. As covered above, it usually holds secrets, so it goes in ",[28,115,116],{},".gitignore",". Otherwise you risk pushing secrets to a remote repo.",[119,120,121],"blockquote",{},[12,122,123,126,127,129],{},[40,124,125],{},"Note","\nIf you accidentally push ",[28,128,30],{},", my recommendation is — rotate every secret in it immediately. The moment you push, assume the secrets are compromised. (Doesn't matter if the repo is private — Git history is forever.)",[12,131,132,134],{},[28,133,30],{}," format is generally:",[136,137,142],"pre",{"className":138,"code":139,"language":140,"meta":141,"style":141},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","KEY=VALUE\n","bash","",[28,143,144],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,146,149,153,157],"span",{"class":147,"line":148},"line",1,[145,150,152],{"class":151},"sMAXC","KEY",[145,154,156],{"class":155},"sWyjQ","=",[145,158,160],{"class":159},"sTRMh","VALUE\n",[12,162,163,164,166,167,170],{},"There's one type of ",[28,165,30],{}," file that we DO commit — ",[28,168,169],{},".env.example",". It has keys but no values:",[136,172,176],{"className":173,"code":174,"language":175,"meta":141,"style":141},"language-env shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","KEY=\n","env",[28,177,178],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,179,180],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,181,174],{},[12,183,184,185,192],{},"The point is to let other developers know which env vars the project needs without leaking the actual values. Each key usually gets a brief comment explaining it. Example: my open-source ",[186,187,191],"a",{"href":188,"rel":189},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fhermione#%E7%92%B0%E5%A2%83%E8%AE%8A%E6%95%B8",[190],"nofollow","Hermione (article in Mandarin)"," project.",[20,194,196],{"id":195},"how-to-use-env","How to use Env",[12,198,199,200,202,203,205],{},"Typical flow — start with ",[28,201,169],{},", copy it to ",[28,204,30],{},", fill in real values:",[136,207,209],{"className":173,"code":208,"language":175,"meta":141,"style":141},"KEY=IsRayNotArray\n",[28,210,211],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,212,213],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,214,208],{},[12,216,217],{},"Then load it with the dotenv package. Usage is one line:",[136,219,223],{"className":220,"code":221,"language":222,"meta":141,"style":141},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","require('dotenv').config()\n","js",[28,224,225],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,226,227,231,234,237,240,243],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,228,230],{"class":229},"sj_SG","require",[145,232,233],{"class":151},"(",[145,235,236],{"class":159},"'dotenv'",[145,238,239],{"class":151},").",[145,241,242],{"class":229},"config",[145,244,245],{"class":151},"()\n",[119,247,248],{},[12,249,250,252,253,256],{},[40,251,125],{},"\nTo load a different .env file, pass a path: ",[28,254,255],{},"config({ path: '.env.development' })",".",[12,258,259,260,263],{},"After that, access via ",[28,261,262],{},"process.env",":",[136,265,267],{"className":220,"code":266,"language":222,"meta":141,"style":141},"console.log(process.env.KEY)\n",[28,268,269],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,270,271,274,277,280,283],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,272,273],{"class":151},"console.",[145,275,276],{"class":229},"log",[145,278,279],{"class":151},"(process.env.",[145,281,152],{"class":282},"sCcAr",[145,284,285],{"class":151},")\n",[12,287,288,289,263],{},"Above is Node.js. In PHP it's ",[28,290,291],{},"getenv()",[136,293,297],{"className":294,"code":295,"language":296,"meta":141,"style":141},"language-php shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","echo getenv('KEY');\n","php",[28,298,299],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,300,301,304,307,309,312],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,302,303],{"class":282},"echo",[145,305,306],{"class":282}," getenv",[145,308,233],{"class":151},[145,310,311],{"class":159},"'KEY'",[145,313,314],{"class":151},");\n",[12,316,317],{},"Most hosting platforms also have an Environment section in their dashboard where you can set env vars directly.",[12,319,320],{},"That's the quick tour of usage.",[20,322,324],{"id":323},"when-to-use-env","When to use Env",[12,326,327],{},"Now the actual question:",[12,329,330],{},"\"When should I use Env?\"",[12,332,333],{},"This is the bit people stumble on. The most common case is sensitive info — keys, passwords, tokens — but you can also stash other commonly-used config in env vars too. Site name, site URL, logo URL — any of those work. Depends on your needs and code structure.",[12,335,336,337,340,341,343],{},"For example, in my ",[186,338,191],{"href":188,"rel":339},[190]," project, I put the OpenAI model name in ",[28,342,30],{},". That way switching models is a one-line config change, not a code change.",[12,345,346,347,349],{},"Env vars cover so many use cases, you can basically think of ",[28,348,30],{}," as a site-wide config file.",[20,351,353],{"id":352},"things-to-watch-out-for","Things to watch out for",[12,355,356],{},"Now for the finer details — differences between frontend and backend usage.",[12,358,359,360,363],{},"Backend first — when your service is deployed, you set env vars in the platform's Environment section. The values get injected into your code at runtime. It's the same shape as your local development setup, just running on the server. And because backend code runs server-side, your env vars are ",[40,361,362],{},"very safe",". I'm emphasizing \"very safe\" here — I'll come back to why.",[12,365,366],{},"Render.com's Environment section as an example:",[12,368,369],{},[15,370],{"alt":42,"src":371},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FmYTQYcw.png",[12,373,374,375,377],{},"Frontend devs use env vars too. With Vite, you create a ",[28,376,30],{}," file and access values like this:",[136,379,381],{"className":220,"code":380,"language":222,"meta":141,"style":141},"console.log(import.meta.env.VITE_KEY);\n",[28,382,383],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,384,385,387,389,391,394,396,399,402,405],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,386,273],{"class":151},[145,388,276],{"class":229},[145,390,233],{"class":151},[145,392,393],{"class":155},"import",[145,395,256],{"class":151},[145,397,398],{"class":282},"meta",[145,400,401],{"class":151},".env.",[145,403,404],{"class":282},"VITE_KEY",[145,406,314],{"class":151},[12,408,409,410,413],{},"Easy enough. But heads up — frontend env vars are ",[40,411,412],{},"not"," a place for sensitive info, because frontend code runs in the browser, meaning everything in your bundle is readable.",[12,415,416,417,420,421,263],{},"What does that look like in practice? Say I create a project with ",[28,418,419],{},"npm create vue@3"," and add a ",[28,422,30],{},[136,424,426],{"className":173,"code":425,"language":175,"meta":141,"style":141},"VITE_API_URL=https:\u002F\u002Fapi.example.com\n",[28,427,428],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,429,430],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,431,425],{},[12,433,434,435,263],{},"And in ",[28,436,437],{},"App.vue",[136,439,443],{"className":440,"code":441,"language":442,"meta":141,"style":141},"language-vue shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cscript setup>\nfetch(import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL)\n  .then(response => response.json())\n  .then(json => console.log(json))\n\u003C\u002Fscript>\n\n\u003Ctemplate>\n  \u003Cdiv>\n    A line of text.\n  \u003C\u002Fdiv>\n\u003C\u002Ftemplate>\n\n\u003Cstyle scoped>\n\u003C\u002Fstyle>\n","vue",[28,444,445,460,481,508,529,539,546,556,567,573,583,592,597,610],{"__ignoreMap":141},[145,446,447,450,454,457],{"class":147,"line":148},[145,448,449],{"class":151},"\u003C",[145,451,453],{"class":452},"sKpQp","script",[145,455,456],{"class":282}," setup",[145,458,459],{"class":151},">\n",[145,461,463,466,468,470,472,474,476,479],{"class":147,"line":462},2,[145,464,465],{"class":229},"fetch",[145,467,233],{"class":151},[145,469,393],{"class":155},[145,471,256],{"class":151},[145,473,398],{"class":282},[145,475,401],{"class":151},[145,477,478],{"class":282},"VITE_API_URL",[145,480,285],{"class":151},[145,482,484,487,490,492,496,499,502,505],{"class":147,"line":483},3,[145,485,486],{"class":151},"  .",[145,488,489],{"class":229},"then",[145,491,233],{"class":151},[145,493,495],{"class":494},"s_sBn","response",[145,497,498],{"class":155}," =>",[145,500,501],{"class":151}," response.",[145,503,504],{"class":229},"json",[145,506,507],{"class":151},"())\n",[145,509,511,513,515,517,519,521,524,526],{"class":147,"line":510},4,[145,512,486],{"class":151},[145,514,489],{"class":229},[145,516,233],{"class":151},[145,518,504],{"class":494},[145,520,498],{"class":155},[145,522,523],{"class":151}," console.",[145,525,276],{"class":229},[145,527,528],{"class":151},"(json))\n",[145,530,532,535,537],{"class":147,"line":531},5,[145,533,534],{"class":151},"\u003C\u002F",[145,536,453],{"class":452},[145,538,459],{"class":151},[145,540,542],{"class":147,"line":541},6,[145,543,545],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":544},true,"\n",[145,547,549,551,554],{"class":147,"line":548},7,[145,550,449],{"class":151},[145,552,553],{"class":452},"template",[145,555,459],{"class":151},[145,557,559,562,565],{"class":147,"line":558},8,[145,560,561],{"class":151},"  \u003C",[145,563,564],{"class":452},"div",[145,566,459],{"class":151},[145,568,570],{"class":147,"line":569},9,[145,571,572],{"class":151},"    A line of text.\n",[145,574,576,579,581],{"class":147,"line":575},10,[145,577,578],{"class":151},"  \u003C\u002F",[145,580,564],{"class":452},[145,582,459],{"class":151},[145,584,586,588,590],{"class":147,"line":585},11,[145,587,534],{"class":151},[145,589,553],{"class":452},[145,591,459],{"class":151},[145,593,595],{"class":147,"line":594},12,[145,596,545],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":544},[145,598,600,602,605,608],{"class":147,"line":599},13,[145,601,449],{"class":151},[145,603,604],{"class":452},"style",[145,606,607],{"class":282}," scoped",[145,609,459],{"class":151},[145,611,613,615,617],{"class":147,"line":612},14,[145,614,534],{"class":151},[145,616,604],{"class":452},[145,618,459],{"class":151},[12,620,621,622,625,626,263],{},"Then ",[28,623,624],{},"npm run build",". Open the generated ",[28,627,628],{},"dist\u002Findex-xxxx.js",[12,630,631],{},[15,632],{"alt":633,"src":634},"index.js","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FNXUl3pt.png",[12,636,637,638,641],{},"Search for ",[28,639,640],{},"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.example.com"," — and there it is, inlined right into the bundle.",[12,643,644],{},[15,645],{"alt":633,"src":646},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F5FGqY8J.png",[12,648,649],{},"That's why frontend env vars shouldn't hold secrets. Use them for non-secret config — API URLs, site titles, feature flags — stuff that's repeated across the app and might change later. That's also why I said \"backend env vars are very safe\" earlier — backend runs on the server, frontend runs in the browser, so anyone who downloads your bundle can see your frontend env values.",[12,651,652],{},"Quick recap of what to remember:",[48,654,655,663,671],{},[51,656,657,659,660,662],{},[28,658,30],{}," doesn't go in version control. Commit only ",[28,661,169],{}," (with empty values) and document the setup in your README.",[51,664,665,666,668,669,256],{},"Don't commit secrets — database passwords, API keys, etc. — make sure ",[28,667,116],{}," covers ",[28,670,30],{},[51,672,673],{},"Frontend env vars shouldn't hold secrets, because the browser sees everything.",[12,675,676],{},"That's about it for env vars.",[12,678,679,680,685],{},"While we're here, a quick plug for writing good READMEs — if your README is bad, nobody can figure out how to set up your project. I shared a ",[186,681,684],{"href":682,"rel":683},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FREADME-Example-Template",[190],"README Template"," you can reference.",[604,687,688],{},"html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}",{"title":141,"searchDepth":462,"depth":462,"links":690},[691,692,693,694,695],{"id":22,"depth":462,"text":23},{"id":34,"depth":462,"text":35},{"id":195,"depth":462,"text":196},{"id":323,"depth":462,"text":324},{"id":352,"depth":462,"text":353},"Misc","2023-02-18 17:29:29","A quick rundown of what .env is and when it makes sense to use one. Covers what env vars are for, the common file conventions (.env.development, .env.production, .env.example), how to load them with dotenv, when to use env vars beyond secrets, and the critical caveat that frontend env vars are NOT a place to store sensitive info — they end up in your built bundle.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it","4",{"title":6,"description":698},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it",[17,42,708,709],"Environment Variables","dotenv",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F02\u002F18\u002Fwhat-is-env-and-when-to-use-it\u002F","njGrpabpoF8revAhRX1_2eyn-hBj6egPROo8Dr9QXWM",{"newer":714,"older":718},{"url":715,"title":716,"date":717},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F06\u002Fvue3-veevalidate-v4-custom-messages\u002F","Vue 3 VeeValidate v4.x Advanced: Customising Error Messages","2023-03-06 16:06:00",{"url":719,"title":720,"date":721},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2023\u002F02\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-why-not-call-hasownproperty-directly\u002F","Why You Shouldn't Call hasOwnProperty Directly (and What ESLint Wants Instead)","2023-02-18 16:54:44",[723,728,733],{"url":724,"title":725,"date":726,"readingMinutes":727},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":729,"title":730,"date":731,"readingMinutes":732},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":734,"title":735,"date":736,"readingMinutes":703},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00",1784010282004]